# Task Management System API

A modular FastAPI-based Task Manager with MongoDB or JSON file storage.

## Setup

1. Install dependencies:
    pip install -r requirements.txt

2. To enable MongoDB, set MONGO_URI as an environment variable.
   Otherwise, local `tasks.json` will be used.

3. Start the API server:
    uvicorn app:app --reload

## API Requests

- Create a task:  
  POST /tasks  
  Request Body:  
  {
    "title": "Sample Task",
    "description": "Details here"
  }
- List tasks:  
  GET /tasks
- Mark completed:  
  PUT /tasks/{id}
- Delete a task:  
  DELETE /tasks/{id}

## Testing

Run:
    python -m unittest discover tests

## Assumptions

- Uses UUID for task IDs.
- MongoDB is used if `MONGO_URI` is set; else JSON file storage.
